{
  "info": {
    "name": "MUFG HRT POC — IDG API Collection",
    "description": "High-Risk Transaction POC — PingGateway (IDG) API endpoints for EIP / Client API Gateway integration.\n\nFlow:\n1. POST /api/authenticate → get xsmid\n2. DSH performs AIC SSO + HRT step-up + OAuth (AIC side)\n3. POST /api/validate → validate JWT + xsmid → APPROVED\n\nAll calls are to PingGateway (IDG). AIC calls are handled internally by DSH/SDK.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_postman_id": "mufg-hrt-poc-idg-v1"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "IDG_BASE_URL",
      "value": "http://localhost:9090",
      "description": "PingGateway (IDG) base URL. Replace with client environment IDG URL."
    },
    {
      "key": "xsmid",
      "value": "",
      "description": "Auto-populated from /api/authenticate response"
    },
    {
      "key": "jwt",
      "value": "",
      "description": "id_token JWT — set manually after DSH completes OAuth flow"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Step 1 — Health Check",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "IDG Hello (Health Check)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('IDG is reachable', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "console.log('IDG Health Check:', pm.response.code, pm.response.text());"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{IDG_BASE_URL}}/hello",
              "host": ["{{IDG_BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["hello"]
            },
            "description": "Verify PingGateway is running and reachable.\n\nExpected: 200 OK with IDG version/status info."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Step 2 — Generate xsmid",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /api/authenticate — Generate xsmid",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('xsmid is present', function() {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.xsmid).to.be.a('string');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.xsmid).to.have.lengthOf.above(10);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Auto-save xsmid to collection variable",
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.xsmid) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('xsmid', json.xsmid);",
                  "    console.log('xsmid saved:', json.xsmid);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"amount\": 9000,\n  \"currency\": \"USD\",\n  \"toAccount\": \"ACCT-9876-5432\",\n  \"fromAccount\": \"ACCT-1234-5678\",\n  \"deviceId\": \"DTB-BROWSER-001\",\n  \"browserInfo\": \"Chrome/126 Windows\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{IDG_BASE_URL}}/api/authenticate",
              "host": ["{{IDG_BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["api", "authenticate"]
            },
            "description": "DTB calls IDG to generate a unique transaction identifier (xsmid) for the High-Risk Transaction.\n\nIDG generates a UUID and returns it as xsmid.\n\nThe xsmid is automatically saved to the collection variable for use in Step 3.\n\nFlow after this call:\n- DTB passes xsmid to DSH\n- DSH performs AIC step-up + OAuth (handled by DSH/SDK)\n- DSH returns id_token JWT containing xsmid claim\n- DTB calls /api/validate with jwt + xsmid"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK — xsmid generated",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"amount\": 9000,\n  \"currency\": \"USD\",\n  \"toAccount\": \"ACCT-9876-5432\",\n  \"fromAccount\": \"ACCT-1234-5678\",\n  \"deviceId\": \"DTB-BROWSER-001\",\n  \"browserInfo\": \"Chrome/126 Windows\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {"raw": "{{IDG_BASE_URL}}/api/authenticate"}
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "body": "{\n  \"xsmid\": \"9a691a63-de29-4b54-9749-d842cb3554b9\",\n  \"issuedAt\": \"2026-07-15T11:22:00Z\",\n  \"expiresIn\": 3600\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Step 3 — Validate JWT",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /api/validate — Validate JWT + xsmid",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Verify xsmid is set",
                  "var xsmid = pm.collectionVariables.get('xsmid');",
                  "if (!xsmid) {",
                  "    console.warn('WARNING: xsmid not set — run Step 2 first');",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "// Verify jwt is set",
                  "var jwt = pm.collectionVariables.get('jwt');",
                  "if (!jwt) {",
                  "    console.warn('WARNING: jwt not set — complete DSH OAuth flow first');",
                  "    console.warn('After DSH callback, copy id_token and set jwt variable');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Decision is APPROVED', function() {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.valid).to.be.true;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.decision).to.equal('APPROVED');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('xsmid matches', function() {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    var reqXsmid = pm.collectionVariables.get('xsmid');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.xsmid).to.equal(reqXsmid);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('acr is HRT', function() {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.acr).to.equal('HRT');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "console.log('Validation Result:', json.decision);",
                  "console.log('Match Method:', json.matchMethod);",
                  "console.log('userId:', json.userId);",
                  "console.log('acr:', json.acr);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jwt\": \"{{jwt}}\",\n  \"xsmid\": \"{{xsmid}}\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{IDG_BASE_URL}}/api/validate",
              "host": ["{{IDG_BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["api", "validate"]
            },
            "description": "DTB sends the id_token JWT and xsmid to IDG for validation.\n\nIDG calls AIC /oauth2/idtokeninfo to:\n1. Verify JWT signature (RS256)\n2. Verify issuer (AIC)\n3. Verify audience (ig-poc-client)\n4. Verify expiry\n5. Read xsmid claim from JWT\n6. Match xsmid from request with xsmid in JWT\n7. Verify acr=HRT (confirms HRTStepUpJourney ran)\n\nPrerequisites:\n- Run Step 2 first to get xsmid (auto-saved)\n- Complete DSH OAuth flow to get JWT\n- Set 'jwt' collection variable with id_token value\n\nMatch Methods:\n- JWT_CLAIM: xsmid found as plain claim in JWT (primary)\n- S_HASH: xsmid verified via s_hash = base64url(SHA256(xsmid)[0:16]) (fallback)"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 APPROVED — xsmid matched via JWT claim",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"jwt\": \"<id_token>\",\n  \"xsmid\": \"9a691a63-de29-4b54-9749-d842cb3554b9\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {"raw": "{{IDG_BASE_URL}}/api/validate"}
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "body": "{\n  \"valid\": true,\n  \"decision\": \"APPROVED\",\n  \"xsmid\": \"9a691a63-de29-4b54-9749-d842cb3554b9\",\n  \"userId\": \"ffa2c3a2-5cbf-4144-85c5-00b805389fb6\",\n  \"acr\": \"HRT\",\n  \"expiresAt\": 1784131424,\n  \"matchMethod\": \"JWT_CLAIM\",\n  \"message\": \"HRT transaction validated successfully\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "200 APPROVED — xsmid matched via s_hash",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"jwt\": \"<id_token>\",\n  \"xsmid\": \"9a691a63-de29-4b54-9749-d842cb3554b9\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {"raw": "{{IDG_BASE_URL}}/api/validate"}
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "body": "{\n  \"valid\": true,\n  \"decision\": \"APPROVED\",\n  \"xsmid\": \"9a691a63-de29-4b54-9749-d842cb3554b9\",\n  \"userId\": \"ffa2c3a2-5cbf-4144-85c5-00b805389fb6\",\n  \"acr\": \"HRT\",\n  \"expiresAt\": 1784131424,\n  \"matchMethod\": \"S_HASH\",\n  \"message\": \"HRT transaction validated via s_hash binding\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "401 REJECTED — Token expired",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"jwt\": \"<expired_id_token>\",\n  \"xsmid\": \"9a691a63-de29-4b54-9749-d842cb3554b9\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {"raw": "{{IDG_BASE_URL}}/api/validate"}
              },
              "status": "Unauthorized",
              "code": 401,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "body": "{\n  \"valid\": false,\n  \"error\": \"TOKEN_INVALID\",\n  \"message\": \"AIC rejected id_token — status: 400\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "401 REJECTED — xsmid mismatch",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"jwt\": \"<id_token>\",\n  \"xsmid\": \"wrong-xsmid-value\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {"raw": "{{IDG_BASE_URL}}/api/validate"}
              },
              "status": "Unauthorized",
              "code": 401,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "body": "{\n  \"valid\": false,\n  \"error\": \"XSMID_MISMATCH\",\n  \"message\": \"xsmid does not match JWT\",\n  \"requestXsmid\": \"wrong-xsmid-value\",\n  \"jwtXsmid\": \"9a691a63-de29-4b54-9749-d842cb3554b9\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "400 BAD REQUEST — Missing params",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"jwt\": \"<id_token>\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {"raw": "{{IDG_BASE_URL}}/api/validate"}
              },
              "status": "Bad Request",
              "code": 400,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "body": "{\n  \"valid\": false,\n  \"error\": \"MISSING_PARAMS\",\n  \"message\": \"jwt and xsmid are required\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Step 4 — Negative Tests",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Validate — Wrong xsmid (should REJECT)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 401', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(401);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Decision is REJECTED', function() {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.valid).to.be.false;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.error).to.equal('XSMID_MISMATCH');",
                  "});",
                  "console.log('Negative test PASSED — wrong xsmid correctly rejected');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jwt\": \"{{jwt}}\",\n  \"xsmid\": \"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000\"\n}",
              "options": {"raw": {"language": "json"}}
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{IDG_BASE_URL}}/api/validate",
              "host": ["{{IDG_BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["api", "validate"]
            },
            "description": "Negative test — send valid JWT but WRONG xsmid.\nIDG should reject with XSMID_MISMATCH.\nVerifies that xsmid binding is enforced."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Validate — No JWT (should reject 400)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 400', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(400);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Error is MISSING_PARAMS', function() {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.error).to.equal('MISSING_PARAMS');",
                  "});",
                  "console.log('Negative test PASSED — missing jwt correctly rejected');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"xsmid\": \"{{xsmid}}\"\n}",
              "options": {"raw": {"language": "json"}}
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{IDG_BASE_URL}}/api/validate",
              "host": ["{{IDG_BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["api", "validate"]
            },
            "description": "Negative test — send xsmid without jwt.\nIDG should reject with 400 MISSING_PARAMS."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Validate — Tampered JWT (should reject)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 401', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(401);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Token rejected', function() {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.valid).to.be.false;",
                  "});",
                  "console.log('Negative test PASSED — tampered JWT correctly rejected');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jwt\": \"eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiJ9.TAMPERED_PAYLOAD.INVALID_SIGNATURE\",\n  \"xsmid\": \"{{xsmid}}\"\n}",
              "options": {"raw": {"language": "json"}}
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{IDG_BASE_URL}}/api/validate",
              "host": ["{{IDG_BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["api", "validate"]
            },
            "description": "Negative test — send tampered JWT with invalid signature.\nIDG calls AIC /idtokeninfo which rejects it.\nVerifies cryptographic validation is enforced."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
